hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: We've got a joint account genetidyne There are plenty of options for the company – it could ride out its difficulties and try to push its newer phones, it could go private, it could find another company to partner with, it could sell entirely or it could sell some of its assets. Boosting BlackBerry to its former place atop the smartphone market could be difficult, to say the least, and nearly unprecedented, Snyder points out. Motorola is one of the very few mobile phone companies to boost itself out of the doldrums, he says, and even then, the company shortly split, with Google eventually buying Motorola Mobility.
